author: detroitnews.com
title: Georgia running back Kurt Taylor commits to Michigan
text:
Jim Harbaugh joins running back Kurt Tucker, who has committed to Michigan for 2017. (Photo: twitter) 
In the midst of rivalry week, Michigan has added another recruit: Covington (Ga.) Newton High running back Kurt Taylor, according to The Wolverine.com.
Taylor, who is 5-foot-9 and 201 pounds, is ranked as the 19th running back nationally. He was recruited by Tyrone Wheatley and is Michigan's third commitment for 2017.
After Speaking with my Parents and Coaches, I am blessed to say, I have committed to The University of Michigan pic.twitter.com/nZa5jQELtD
